label.value: olfactory bulb interneuron fate commitment

value.value: The process in which the developmental fate of a neuroblast becomes restricted such that it will develop into an interneuron residing in the olfactory bulb.

label.value: olfactory bulb interneuron development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an interneuron residing in the olfactory bulb, from its initial commitment, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label.value: cerebral cortex GABAergic interneuron differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a GABAergic interneuron residing in the cerebral cortex.

label.value: cerebral cortex GABAergic interneuron fate commitment

value.value: The process in which the developmental fate of a neuroblast becomes restricted such that it will develop into a GABAergic interneuron residing in the cerebral cortex.

label.value: cerebral cortex GABAergic interneuron development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a cerebral cortex GABAergic interneuron over time, from initial commitment to its fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label.value: cerebral cortex neuron differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a neuron residing in the cerebral cortex.

label.value: forebrain astrocyte differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of an astrocyte residing in the forebrain. An astrocyte is the most abundant type of glial cell. Astrocytes provide support for neurons and regulate the environment in which they function.

label.value: forebrain astrocyte development

value.value: The process aimed at the progression of an astrocyte that resides in the forebrain, from initial commitment of the cell to its fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell. An astrocyte is the most abundant type of glial cell. Astrocytes provide support for neurons and regulate the environment in which they function.

label.value: commitment of multipotent stem cells to neuronal lineage in forebrain

value.value: The initial commitment of cells whereby the developmental fate of a cell becomes restricted such that it will develop into some type of neuron in the forebrain.

label.value: fibroblast growth factor receptor signaling pathway involved in forebrain neuron fate commitment

value.value: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a fibroblast growth factor receptor binding to one of its physiological ligands that contributes to the commitment of a neuroblast to a neuronal fate. The neuron will reside in the forebrain.

label.value: ventricular zone cell fate commitment

value.value: The commitment of neuroblast to become a basal progenitor cell. Basal progenitor cells are neuronal precursor cells that are committed to becoming neurons.

label.value: early neuron fate commitment in forebrain

value.value: The commitment of neuroepithelial cell to become a neuron that will reside in the forebrain.

label.value: commitment of neuronal cell to specific neuron type in forebrain

value.value: The commitment of neuronal precursor cells to become specialized types of neurons in the forebrain.

label.value: rostrocaudal neural tube patterning

value.value: The process in which the neural tube is divided into specific regions along the rostrocaudal axis.

label.value: dorsal/ventral neural tube patterning

value.value: The process in which the neural tube is regionalized in the dorsoventral axis.

label.value: forebrain-midbrain boundary formation

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the creation of the forebrain-midbrain boundary.

label.value: hindbrain-spinal cord boundary formation

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the formation of the hindbrain-spinal cord boundary.

label.value: fibroblast growth factor receptor signaling pathway involved in spinal cord anterior/posterior pattern formation

value.value: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a fibroblast growth factor receptor binding to one of its physiological ligands that results in the spatial identity of regions along the anterior-posterior axis of the spinal cord.

label.value: smoothened signaling pathway involved in ventral spinal cord patterning

value.value: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of activation of the transmembrane protein Smoothened that results in the spatial identity of regions along the dorsal-ventral axis of the spinal cord.

label.value: retinoic acid metabolic process in spinal cord anterior-posterior patterning

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways involving the synthesis and degradation of retionic acid that results in the spatial identity of regions along the anterior-posterior axis of the spinal cord.

label.value: negative regulation of smoothened signaling pathway involved in ventral spinal cord patterning

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of smoothened signaling that is involved in the patterns of cell differentiation in the ventral spinal cord.

label.value: neural tube development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the neural tube over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The mature structure of the neural tube exists when the tube has been segmented into the forebrain, midbrain, hindbrain and spinal cord regions. In addition neural crest has budded away from the epithelium.

label.value: inductive cell-cell signaling between paraxial mesoderm and motor neuron precursors

value.value: Short range signaling between cells of the paraxial mesoderm and motor neuron precursors in the spinal cord that specifies the fate of the motor column neuron precursors along the anterior-posterior axis.

label.value: somatic motor neuron fate commitment

value.value: The commitment of unspecified motor neurons to specific motor neuron cell along the anterior-posterior axis of the spinal cord and their capacity to differentiate into specific motor neurons.

label.value: regulation of cell proliferation in dorsal spinal cord

value.value: The process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation in the dorsal spinal cord.

label.value: cell proliferation in hindbrain ventricular zone

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population in the hindbrain region that is adjacent to the ventricular cavity.

label.value: cell proliferation in external granule layer

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of neuroblasts resulting in the expansion of a cell population in the external granule layer of the hindbrain. The external granule layer is the layer that originates from the rostral half of the rhombic lip in the first rhombomere.

label.value: cerebellar Purkinje cell precursor proliferation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of neuroblasts that will give rise to Purkinje cells. A Purkinje cell is an inhibitory GABAergic neuron found in the cerebellar cortex that projects to the deep cerebellar nuclei and brain stem.

label.value: Golgi cell precursor proliferation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of neuroblasts that will give rise to Golgi cells. A Golgi cell is an inhibitory GABAergic interneuron found in the cerebellar cortex.

label.value: deep nuclear neuron precursor proliferation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of neuroblasts that will give rise to deep nuclear neurons.

label.value: basket cell precursor proliferation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of neuroblasts that will give rise to basket cells. A cerebellar basket cell is an inhibitory GABAergic interneuron found in the cerebellar cortex.

label.value: stellate cell precursor proliferation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of neuroblasts that will give rise to stellate cells. A cerebellar stellate cell is an inhibitory GABAergic interneuron found in the cerebellar cortex.

label.value: cerebellar granule cell precursor proliferation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of neuroblasts that will give rise to granule cells. A granule cell is a glutamatergic interneuron found in the cerebellar cortex.

label.value: rostral hindbrain neuronal precursor cell proliferation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of neuroblasts that will give rise to neurons of the lateral pontine nucleus and the locus ceruleus.

label.value: hindbrain radial glia guided cell migration

value.value: The radially directed movement of a cell along radial glial cells in the hindbrain. Radial migration refers to a directed movement from the internal ventricular area to the outer surface of the hindbrain.

label.value: radial glia guided migration of cerebellar granule cell

value.value: The inward migration of postmitotic granule cells along a radial glial cell from the external granule layer to the internal granule cell layer.

label.value: hindbrain tangential cell migration

value.value: The migration of a cell in the hindbrain in which cells move orthogonal to the direction of radial migration.

label.value: cerebellar granule cell precursor tangential migration

value.value: The early migration of granule cell precursors in which cells move orthogonal to the direction of radial migration and ultimately cover the superficial zone of the cerebellar primordium.

label.value: regulation of cerebellar granule cell precursor proliferation

value.value: The process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of granule cell precursor proliferation.

label.value: cerebellar Purkinje cell-granule cell precursor cell signaling involved in regulation of granule cell precursor cell proliferation

value.value: The process that mediates the transfer of information from Purkinje cells to granule cell precursors resulting in an increase in rate of granule cell precursor cell proliferation.

label.value: smoothened signaling pathway involved in regulation of cerebellar granule cell precursor cell proliferation

value.value: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of activation of the transmembrane protein Smoothened in cerebellar granule cells that contributes to the regulation of proliferation of the cells.

label.value: extracellular matrix-granule cell signaling involved in regulation of granule cell precursor proliferation

value.value: The process that mediates the transfer of information from the extracellular matrix to granule cell precursors resulting in a decrease in rate of granule cell precursor cell proliferation.

label.value: positive regulation of cerebellar granule cell precursor proliferation

value.value: The process that activates or increases the rate or extent of granule cell precursor proliferation.

label.value: negative regulation of cerebellar granule cell precursor proliferation

value.value: The process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of granule cell precursor proliferation.

label.value: radial glia guided migration of Purkinje cell

value.value: The migration of postmitotic a Purkinje cell along radial glial cells from the ventricular zone to the Purkinje cell layer.

label.value: formation of radial glial scaffolds

value.value: The formation of scaffolds from a radial glial cell. The scaffolds are used as a substrate for the radial migration of cells.

label.value: neuronal-glial interaction involved in hindbrain glial-mediated radial cell migration

value.value: The changes in adhesion between a neuronal cell and a glial cell as a component of the process of hindbrain glial-mediated radial cell migration.

label.value: deep nuclear neuron cell migration

value.value: The directed movement of a deep nuclear neuron from the ventricular zone to the deep hindbrain nuclei.

label.value: outward migration of deep nuclear neurons

value.value: The directed movement of a deep nuclear neuron from their ventrolateral origin to a rostrodorsal region of the cerebellar plate.

label.value: inward migration of deep nuclear neurons

value.value: The directed movement of a deep nuclear neuron from the rostrodorsal region of the cerebellar plate to their final more ventral position.
